category=Getting Started
description=<p>Open Anything is a simple utility that lets you open any file on disk and display the text portion of the file.  You can edit the text and save it out to a text file. </p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The Video Tutorial shows you how to use this Sample Project, and how to take it apart to understand how it works or copy portions of it for use in your own applications.  The PDF contains the same information as the Video, in printable form.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><font face="Lucida Grande" size="11"><a href="video:Open Anything">Click here to go to the corresponding video and PDF</a></font></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>We recommend you to have explored the introductory video tutorials so you have a basic understanding of how Revolution works before you start on the Sample Projects.</p>
level=2
name=Open Anything
title=Open Anything - display text from any file
topics=<p>The key topics covered in this Project are:</p>\n<p>   - How to bring up a system file selector dialog ot open or save a file</p>\n<p>   - How to read a file</p>\n<p>   - How to eliminate non-text characters from a file</p>